%% Diagram: Script and CSS blocking chain during HTML parsing
%% Type: sequence
%%{init: {'htmlLabels': false}}%%
sequenceDiagram
    participant P as HTML Parser
    participant N as Network
    participant CSS as CSS / CSSOM
    participant JS as JS Engine

    P->>P: Parse <head>
    P->>N: Request stylesheet
    P->>P: Continue parsing (CSS does not block parser)
    P->>P: Encounter <script src="app.js">
    Note over P: Parser pauses
    P->>N: Request app.js
    N-->>P: app.js bytes
    Note over P,JS: Script ready, but CSSOM not complete
    N-->>CSS: stylesheet bytes
    CSS-->>CSS: Build CSSOM
    CSS-->>JS: CSSOM ready
    JS->>JS: Execute app.js
    Note over JS: May call getComputedStyle()<br/>or document.write()
    JS-->>P: Execution complete
    P->>P: Resume parsing
